Conservation Status:
—Vulnerable (VU, D2) according to the IUCN Red List guidelines (
IUCN 2019
). Although the species is solely known from restricted areas in mountain tops with a small extent of occurrence (EOO <
100 km
2
) and area of occupancy (AOO <
10 km
2
), its distribution is included in a State Park, favouring its conservation. However, stochastic events (such as intense fires or drought) could drive the species to CR (Critically Endangered) in a short time.
